Question.TranslatedText:
Subject must meet ALL of the inclusion criteria to be included in the study.

1. Provision of signed and dated informed consent form.
2. Male or female, aged 18-65 years (inclusive).
3. Negative urine pregnancy test for females of childbearing potential.
4. Inclusion criteria for female subjects:
a. Postmenopausal for at least 2 years, or
b. Surgically sterile, or
c. Abstinence from heterosexual intercourse throughout the study, or
d. Willingness to use highly effective contraception throughout the study and for 6 months after the last dose of the study medication.
5. Male subjects must agree to use a highly effective contraception and not to donate sperm throughout the study and for 6 months after the last dose of the study medication.

Alias.Name: Specify the inclusion criteria not met

Question.TranslatedText:
Subject must NOT meet ANY of the exclusion criteria to be included in the study.

1. HCV or HIV coinfection.
2. Previous or unstable concurrent diseases or conditions that prevent subject’s enrolment into the study.
3. Patients with mental disorders or social circumstances that preclude them from following protocol requirements.
4. One or more additional known primary or secondary causes of liver disease, other than hepatitis B
5. History of solid organ transplantation.
6. Current alcohol abuse or alcohol abuse within 6 months prior to enrolment in this study; past or current drug addict.
7. Pregnant or breast-feeding females.
8. Participation in another clinical study with investigational drugs within 30 days prior to randomization.
9. Inability to follow protocol requirements and undergo all protocol procedures.
10. Uncontrolled cardiovascular disorders within 6 months before screening.
11. History of autoimmune disorder
12. Presence or history of significant psychiatric disorder (e.g. severe depression, suicide attempt, severe neurosis or cognitive disorder).
